#Text=Understand Life
#Text=So far , I have finished one way to develop life and universe understanding .
#Text=More are coming .
#Text=Please comment on anything you think is a good method .
#Text=Or , put you method into the comments box .
#Text=Which way ?
#Text=Who knows ?
#Text=Do you even understand the questions you are asking about questions ?
#Text=But is the question really about questions ?
#Text=Dig deep , always deep .
#Text=Unless , it 's digging you in deep .
#Text=Understand the universe and all it 's life , let it understand you .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Yoga
#Text=I also at a point thought that yoga was pointless .
#Text=Then , I realized how much it it helped me and gave me a way to stay peaceful and calm the rest of the day .
#Text=However if this does n't work for you , then there are other ways .
#Text=However , I encourage trying it at least once .
#Text=Find a wide and spacious area where you can set up .
#Text=This is a very important step , because small areas can do the opposite of give you meaning , and instead just make you feel stuck and unimportant .
#Text=This is not what you want .
#Text=Lay down several mats , even if it is just you .
#Text=Having more room than you need is a good thing , and maybe even essential , depending on the person .
#Text=Make sure that the mats are both thick , and soft , as if you could dig into the endless meaning of life through it .
#Text=Turn on some soothing music .
#Text=Now , when I say " soothing music " , I mean soothing to you .
#Text=If rock and roll or heavy metal are your favorite kinds of music , go for it !
#Text=It does not have to be slow , or quiet .
#Text=Create a motivation .
#Text=Do not buy therapy cards , or any kind of idea givers .
#Text=Think of one yourself , otherwise you 'll find that you are convincing yourself that something someone else said is you .
#Text=That is not always true , and it takes a lot to figure out what exactly is real , and what is just a mindset .
#Text=Either do poses , or lie down thinking .
#Text=Ask yourself questions like , How important to me is my motavation ?
#Text=What would change in the world without me ?
#Text=Suppose I put all my effort into improving the world .
#Text=How would it change ?
#Text=How much am I capable of ?
#Text=Do I have any beliefs or religions ?
#Text=How do they effect how I think or act ?
#Text=This should lead to more questions , unless you are n't really thinking .
#Text=Do n't think too hard , or it will tire you and distract you from obvious answers .
#Text=If this takes you hours , it is OK .
#Text=Do n't worry about work , or appointments , anything you are late for .
#Text=It is just you .
#Text=What is more important ?
#Text=Full Meaning or Jobs ?
